{
  "doc_id": "28313",
  "text": "The stressors encountered as a direct result of the experience of living with dementia or caring for a family member with dementia are labeled as primary stressors in the SPM. A fundamental primary stressor from both versions of the SPM is the PWD's cognitive function [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Additionally, for family caregivers, the strain (or role overload/burden) that arises directly from caring for a family member with dementia is of primary importance to the stress process [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Both cognitive impairment [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] and care-related strain [CITATION_7] have also been found to be determinants of PWD-family caregiver incongruence in the broader literature.",
